s looking for a church with deeply rooted religious convictions with adult baptism and a church where the members still bring their Bibles to We are so confused here and we're drifting around trying to find a place where we both feel loved and can express our faith honestly and without If anyone can point us in a direction we'd be thrilled I'm afraid that it will be very hard for me to go back to C of C and even harder for me to stay churchless for any responses would be welcome the diel family I would think somewhere in the Baptist spectrum you might find what you're looking However the issue is probably more one of the flavor of the specific local churches in your area than the denomination Baptists cover quite a Adult baptism sort of narrows your choices on the more liberal end of the Historically that's been associated with movements that have the character you're trying to clh